author: rhuijben
msg: Avoid one more database transaction in the update editor by reading the
'entry-props' when opening the directory and storing them in the
baton. Do the same things for files for correctness, but in practice we
always receive new information for files.
(dir_baton): Add 3 variables and rewrap an unrelated comment.
(file_baton): Add 3 variables and rewrap an unrelated comment.
(open_directory): Fill dir baton. Store in the right pool.
(close_directory): Use information from baton instead of reading BASE again.
(close_file): Make entry-props handling similar to directories. Update user.
